Oh man. This is the first bite of food I had in Chicago.  I've tried all of their tacos and the fish and al pastor are my favorites. Their burrito is excellent and so is pretty much everything else on the menu.  What makes Chilango special is their sauces. They serve a mild, medium and spicy sauce. I usually drench my tacos in the mild and medium sauce and I swear it's the best taco I've had anywhere in Chicago. It's amazing how good the sauces taste.  When you're done with the tacos and you need some dessert, the Nutella banana empanada should do nicely. Careful tho, it's hot af, filled with gooey Nutella and sliced ripe bananas
